## Markdown

### Block formatting options

Headings are added using hashes to signify the heading level - for example, `## Heading 2` for a h2.
You can see examples of headings in use on this page - the h1 as the page title, and h2 and h3 above this paragraph.

Code styling can be used in headings if need be but does alter the perceived size of the text.

> Blockquotes can be added using a '\>' chevron/greater than symbol at the start of a line.

